{
  "texts": [
    "However, HTML remains a markup language optimized for rendering rather than for training language models.",
    "To maximize the utility of the extracted content for downstream AI applications, we require a format that is both semantically rich and compact.",
    "This section presents MinerU-HTML's two-stage formatting pipeline that transforms Main-HTML into AI-ready representations.We adopt a two-stage conversion strategy with an intermediate representation.",
    "First, we parse Main-HTML into a structured content list-a JSON-based representation that explicitly categorizes each semantic unit by type (e.g., title, paragraph, code block, table, formula).",
    "This intermediate representation enables flexible filtering and format-specific rendering."
  ]
}